Process and workflow:

**Slash commands (AGENT EXECUTION DIRECTIVE):** When the user invokes a slash command (any file under `.cursor/commands/`), you are receiving an EXECUTABLE WORKFLOW. You MUST: (1) EXECUTE each step sequentially — read files, run shell commands, write documents, git operations — as specified. (2) DO NOT summarize the command or describe what it "would do"; the function body IS your instruction set. (3) For start/end commands, follow `.cursor/commands/tiers/START_END_PLAYBOOK_STRUCTURE.md` and the command-to-entry-point table; resolve the command name to the composite module (feature.ts, phase.ts, session.ts, task.ts under tiers/<tier>/composite/), invoke the exported function with params gathered from context and prompts, use result.outcome.nextAction. For /accepted-proceed and /accepted-code: the agent does not run or invoke these commands — **the user** runs them (e.g. the user runs the slash command in the UI). After **task-start**, direct the user to **/accepted-code** only (not /accepted-proceed). After feature/phase/session start, use **/accepted-proceed** as the command output says. The agent fills the planning doc and guide using context and prompts the user to run the command when ready. When the user has run /accepted-proceed or /accepted-code, present result.controlPlaneDecision.message and handle outcome per playbook. Do not run the command file from the shell as the primary workflow. (4) Present any prompts specified and wait for user response; format output per any referenced response template. Failure mode to avoid: responding with "This command would do X" — that is summarization, not execution.

**Session structure:** Label session (## Session: [Phase].[Sub-Phase] - [Brief Description]); review previous notes; work one sub-session at a time with checkpoints. End-of-session checklist: (1) Verify app starts (e.g. npm run start:dev), (2) Run linting (e.g. cd client && npm run lint for Vue, cd server && npm run lint for server) and fix errors, (3) Update session log, (4) Update handoff document: ensure required sections are filled (Current Status, Next Action, Transition Context — see `.project-manager/REQUIRED_DOC_SECTIONS.md`), and Last Updated, (5) Prompt user for commit and push when checks pass, (6) Agent hand-off: compact prompt @[HANDOFF_DOCUMENT] Continue [project] - start Sub-Session X.Y.Z (Description). See: VUE_MIGRATION_SESSION_GUIDE.md, VUE_MIGRATION_HANDOFF.md. Exception: Quick fixes may skip full structure but still verify app starts and linting passes.

**User choices (present in chat):** When a tier command result requires a user choice, the command output includes a **User choice required** block with a message and numbered options. **Present that block in chat** so the user sees the message and options clearly (e.g. as markdown). Direct the user to run the corresponding slash command (e.g. `/accepted-push`, `/task-start 6.4.4.1`) or to reply with their choice (e.g. "Retry", "Skip"). Do not call any external "AskQuestion" tool — choices are shown in the command output and you present them in chat.

This applies to: cascade confirmation, verification options, failure retry/audit-fix/skip, reopen options, and uncommitted-changes commit/stash. Command-gated flows (context_gathering, planning_doc_incomplete, guide_fill_pending, guide_incomplete, pending_push_confirmation) use `/accepted-proceed` (feature/phase/session), `/accepted-code` (task), `/accepted-push`, or `/skip-push` instead.

**Testing suspended:** Do NOT create, modify, or run test files. Testing is disabled project-wide (TEST_ENABLED=false in .env) and suspended until Phase 3.0 of LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md. The harness test steps are no-ops. Do not write tests proactively even if guides or playbooks mention testing goals — those are placeholders for Phase 3.0.

**Vue-only development:** All new features and changes in the Vue frontend (frontend root directory). React codebase removed (archived in react-codebase-archive-2025-11-26). All development focuses exclusively on the Vue application.

**Migration authority:** Do NOT run `npm run migrate`, `npm run db:reset`, `npx sequelize-cli db:migrate`, or any other migration/DDL command unless `DB_HOST` in `server/.env.development` is `localhost` or `127.0.0.1`. When `DB_HOST` points to a remote IP, this machine is a consumer of a shared database — only the host machine runs migrations. You may author migration files and commit them; execution happens elsewhere. The migration scripts enforce this with a hard guard, but do not attempt to bypass it.

**Tier workflow skill:** For detailed agent behavior on tier slash commands, control-plane messages, reason codes, cascade, session structure, and handoffs, see `.cursor/skills/tier-workflow-agent/SKILL.md` (and `reason-codes.md` in the same folder).

**Harness charter:** Document I/O (`DocumentManager`), idempotent logs, and git behavior (tier-start vs tier-end) are summarized in `.project-manager/HARNESS_CHARTER.md` §4 (Current implementation notes).
